  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thessaloniki Day Care Center</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1) The living conditions of the refugees are improved.
1.2) The sense of security of the refugees is improved.
 
2.1) Stress and traumata symptoms of the refugees are reduced. 
2.2) Self esteem, mutual trust, empathy of the refugees and cooperation among them are improved. 
2.3) Refugees are enabled to determine their lives. 
2.4) The capacity of volunteers and staff to communicate and cooperate among them and to deal with refugee-related issues is improved. 
2.5) Practical information on aspects of everyday life is provided to the refugees. 

3.1) The nutrition of the refugees is improved. 
3.2) Hygiene of the refugees is improved.
 
4.1) The refugees&apos; sense of acceptance by the host community is improved. 
4.2) The host community is sensitized towards the refugees and thus prepared to accept them. 
4.3) The welcoming of the refugees by the local community is increased</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Day Care Center will provide, on a daily basis, meals and, in a weekly basis, it will offer hygienic services, such as laundry cycles. Additionally, it will provide psycho-social support while it will also organize various multi-cultural events in order to increase the interaction between the host community and the refugees as well as to improve cohesion within the society. At the same time, housing will be provided for the refugees who are entitled to family reunification in Germany and Austria, while they wait in Thessaloniki for the process to be completed.</narrative>
  </description>
